Description: Body sherd from East Greek grey ware large pottery vessel, probably krater or dinos; dark grey fabric with mica inclusions; dark grey slip and inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: Joins British Museum 1965,0930.410 and probably belongs to the same vessel as British Museum 1965,0930.406; 1965,0930.407; 1965,0930.409.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.058)
